medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The pregnancy was uneventful until the 24th week when the patient was found to be in labor during a doctor visit. She had no symptoms at the time, despite being in labor, and was transferred to a higher care facility. Antenatal corticosteroids were administered, and she underwent an emergency cesarean delivery at 25 weeks and 3 days, during which she was found to be fully dilated with the fetus in the birth canal in breech position.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Mrs C has a history of 4 pregnancies, with 3 miscarriages before 7 weeks and 3 dilatation and curettage procedures. She underwent a tonsillectomy as a child. Otherwise, she is healthy.
medical_history.social_history: Mrs C has smoked intermittently since her teenage years, quitting once for 13 years. During her pregnancy, she reduced smoking to about 1 cigarette a week. She did not consume alcohol during the pregnancy but drank socially prior to conception.
